const objects and const methods
  const object
    `const Square x{5};`
    this object cannot be modified after creation
      > cannot change its data members
      > cannot call functions that might change it

  const method
    `int area() const { ... }`
    the method promises not to modify the object  
      > can read members 
      > cannot edit members

  const objects can only call const methods

  internally 
    a member function is just a normal function with an extra parameter 
    int area() {}       -> int area(Square* this)
    int area() const {} -> int area( const Square* this)

